org.jcvi.jillion.assembly.clc.cas

Class CasFileParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jcvi.jillion.assembly.clc.cas.CasFileParser
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CasParser

    public final class CasFileParser
extends Object
implements CasParser
    CasFileParser is a CasParser that can parse CLC .cas formated files that were created using either the legacy clc_ref_assemble_X programs or the newer clc_mapper program. Both programs make slightly different versions of cas files that are not backwards compatible.
    Author:
    dkatzel

      • create

        public static CasParser create(File casFile)
                        throws IOException
        Create a new CasParser instance to parse the given cas formatted file without first validating it. Please note, that the file won't actually be parsed until CasParser.parse(CasFileVisitor) is called. This is the same as calling create(casFile, false) (no validation).
        Parameters:
        casFile - the cas formatted file to parse; can not be null and must exist.
        Returns:
        a new CasParser instance; will never be null.
        Throws:
        IOException - if the casFile does not exist.
        NullPointerException - if casFile is null.
        See Also:
        create(File, boolean)

      • create

        public static CasParser create(File casFile,
                               boolean validate)
                        throws IOException
        Create a new CasParser instance to parse the given cas formatted file.
        Parameters:
        casFile - the cas formatted file to parse; can not be null and must exist.
        validate - validate the cas input data at construction time. If set to true, then this constructor will fail fast if there are discrepancies between what the cas file was assembled with and what the data files currently look like. For example: if an input file no longer has the same number of records or a different number of bases etc. If validation fails, then an IllegalStateException is thrown by this constructor. Validation is very time consuming since all input files must be completely parsed so use validation with care.
        Returns:
        a new CasParser instance; will never be null.
        Throws:
        IOException - if the casFile does not exist.
        NullPointerException - if casFile is null.
        IllegalStateException - if validate is set to true and validation fails.
